# Bilingual Documentation Rules

This project maintains bilingual documentation (English and Chinese). All documentation must be kept in sync.

> **Note**: For command documentation updates triggered by `cmd/*.go` changes, use the `cmd-sync` skill.

## File Naming Convention

- English version: `<name>.md` (e.g., `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`)
- Chinese version: `<name>-zh.md` (e.g., `README-zh.md`, `CHANGELOG-zh.md`)

## Documentation Structure

```
README.md / README-zh.md          # Project overview (kept minimal)
CHANGELOG.md / CHANGELOG-zh.md    # Version history
docs/
  ags.md / ags-zh.md              # Main command documentation
  ags-<cmd>.md / ags-<cmd>-zh.md  # Subcommand documentation
man/                              # Man pages (auto-generated, not committed)
  ags.1, ags-tool.1, ...          # Generated via `make man`
```

## Required Documentation Files

The following documentation files MUST exist in both languages:

| English | Chinese |
|---------|---------|
| `README.md` | `README-zh.md` |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | `CHANGELOG-zh.md` |
| `docs/ags.md` | `docs/ags-zh.md` |
| `docs/ags-tool.md` | `docs/ags-tool-zh.md` |
| `docs/ags-instance.md` | `docs/ags-instance-zh.md` |
| `docs/ags-run.md` | `docs/ags-run-zh.md` |
| `docs/ags-exec.md` | `docs/ags-exec-zh.md` |
| `docs/ags-file.md` | `docs/ags-file-zh.md` |
| `docs/ags-apikey.md` | `docs/ags-apikey-zh.md` |

## Synchronization Rules

1. **Content Parity**: Both language versions must contain equivalent information
2. **Simultaneous Updates**: When updating one version, the other version MUST be updated in the same commit
3. **Structure Consistency**: Both versions should maintain the same document structure (headings, sections, order)

## CHANGELOG Format

Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format:

```markdown
# Changelog / 更新日志

## [Unreleased]

## [x.y.z] - YYYY-MM-DD

### Added
- New feature description

### Changed
- Change description

### Fixed
- Bug fix description

### Removed
- Removed feature description
```

## Rules File Language

All rule files (`.rules/*.mdc`) MUST be written in **English** only.

## Workflow

When making changes that affect documentation:

1. Update the English version first
2. Translate and update the Chinese version
3. Ensure both files are included in the same commit
4. Verify content parity before committing
